Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

So, this results into a schema change check the schema api http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-image-v2.html .

I am not sure about the client upgrades needed but any cached schema on the client side would result into failure for GET calls. I think we have removed that restriction for `list` but `show` would be affected.

My take it go for a full spec on this as we need to bump up minor version of the API, add release & upgrade notes, etc.

These flags become importatt:

    APIImpact
    DocImpact
    UpgradeImpact
    SecurityImapact (depending on the HV host risks associated and potential items for operators awareness -- I am out of sync with the DockerWorld for the moment)

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2

Someone or other will block this again, but I just heard Flavio saying on IRC to block this until spec/lite-spec approved.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1

I'd suggest a test, but I don't see any tests for the other formats (nor a test to ensure that unacceptable formats are blocked).

In any case, I tried it myself with no problems.

Patch Set 2:

Nikhil,

Mind to point out where the APIImpact, UpgradeImpact and SecurityImpact are coming from?

Marked the bug to wishlist.

Patch Set 2:

I'm going to remain neutral on adding docker, but...

I do think we need to find a balance between trying to do things 'the right way' and overhead/not turning off committers. Especially first time committers to Glance.

How would we have felt if the response to our first commit was a '-2', a request for additional stuff that's arguably unrelated, and uncertainty around what the submission procedure is -- maybe a spec's needed, maybe not?

@Mike

Dave's change is specific to the container_format parameter -- which artifacts doesn't use.

Dave only wanted/needed to change this for images. I feel that the artifacts change could have been pushed up as a separate patch, and that it's not something that Dave necessarily needed to own. Similarly with Rally. In fact hardcoding the values in the Rally comment is probably wrong ... since the parameter is configurable the comment is not true in all cases.

@Nikhil

Here is the last time a container_format was added:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/77762/

There was no spec (specs didn't exist) and I don't think that was a problem.


> I am not sure about the client upgrades needed but any cached schema on the client side would result into failure for GET calls. I think we have removed that restriction for `list` but `show` would be affected.

'show' would be affected for cases where you had the old container_formats ('bare', 'ova' etc) cached and you wanted to show an image with 'docker' enabled. So (I think) only cases where 'docker' is required would be affected. In those cases, operators are currently already adding 'docker' to the container_format list because it's a requirement. So, yes, we need to fix the client (caching is probably broken by design), but I don't think there's impact to non-nova-docker deployments here. And I don't think there's any new impact to nova-docker deployments. (If I've got this wrong, please correct me!)

Patch Set 2:

First and foremost, I'm sorry for not commenting before.

I'm not sure  about we needing a full spec for this but I'd like to understand better where Nikhil is coming from so that we can evaluate the proposal.

I'm personally not opposed to add a new container format but I do think we need, at the very least, a lite spec for this. This is the reason I asked to block the patch when Hermanth pointed it out to me. That is, to avoid the patch landing w/o a minimum of review from the drivers team.

I noticed the bug was marked as wishlist and we can review it in our next drivers (or team) meeting.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

This has got enough attention in one of the weekly meetings ( http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/meetings/glance/2015/glance.2015-11-26-14.06.log.txt ). So, we need to decide on the API impact of this. I think if the schema breaks and anyone sourcing the schema notices the break and no version bump to API, it will break the contract. So, I think this needs a minor version bump to the API.

Moving back to -1 from -2 as it will be reviewed upon soon.

Patch Set 2:

I'd like to see this land and I'm happy to do whatever people decide is needed. But as I've not contributed to Glance before a clear outline of what I need to do would be greatly appreciated.
